---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Docs.astro";
---

<Layout title="What - STEREO Internet Toolkit">
  <article style="margin-top: -1px;">
    <h2 id="what" class="mt0">What is STEREO?</h2>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap">
      <div class="w-100 w-50-ns pr3-ns">
        <p>
          Primarily, STEREO is a pragmatic bundle of tools, pre-wired and ready
          for use.
        </p>

        <p>The tools:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.slimframework.com/"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">Slim v4</a
            > (w/
            <a
              href="https://github.com/slimphp/Slim-Psr7"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">Slim PSR-7</a
            >)
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://laravel.com/docs/blade"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">Blade templating</a
            > - using <a
              href="https://github.com/EFTEC/BladeOne"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">BladeOne</a
            > and <a
              href="https://github.com/EFTEC/BladeOneHtml"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">BladeOne HTML</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            View rendering helpers - <a
              href="https://github.com/jyoungblood/stereo-render"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">STEREO Render</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Database handlers - <a
              href="https://github.com/jyoungblood/db-kit"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">DB Kit</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Cookie handlers - <a
              href="https://github.com/delight-im/PHP-Cookie"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">Cookie</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Simple HTTP client - <a
              href="https://github.com/jyoungblood/http-request"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">HTTP Request</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Misc utility functions - <a
              href="https://github.com/jyoungblood/x-utilities"
              class="sys-blue"
              target="_blank">X-Utilities</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/" class="sys-blue" target="_blank"
              >TailwindCSS</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://alpinejs.dev/" class="sys-blue" target="_blank"
              >AlpineJS</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://vitejs.dev/" class="sys-blue" target="_blank"
              >Vite</a
            > & <a href="https://postcss.org/" class="sys-blue" target="_blank"
              >PostCSS</a
            > integration coming soon
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          This toolkit also provides a very simple application structure
          [boilerplate/skeleton] and (forthcoming) opinions and methodology for
          developing applications quickly using these tools. These process are
          not dogmatic, but aim to provide helpful suggestions for "next steps"
          and answers for how to build specific kinds of functionality.
        </p>

        <p>
          In the future this will be a central resource for copy/paste
          components, links to resources, etc.
        </p>

        <p>
          ...all in due time, of course. I'm only one guy and I have a pretty
          busy life.
        </p>

        <p>
          STEREO has developed slowly over the last fifteen-ish years and I'm
          finally getting around to making it more user-friendly to those who
          could benefit. <a href="mailto:jonathan.youngblood@gmail.com"
            >Drop me an email</a
          > if you'd like to get involved.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-100 w-50-ns pl3-ns">
        <img
          class="w-100"
          src="/images/analogy-workflow.jpg"
          alt="Man on his knees in front of a component stereo system"
        />

        <br /><br />

        <div class="embed-container">
          <iframe
            title="YouTube video player"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AnrM4UjaQmY?si=g7Ah6-5X-8vG38os"
            frameborder="0"
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <br /><br />

    <h2>ETHOS / GOALS</h2>

    <p>
      - reliable "pre-wired" base system built with technology that isn’t
      changing all the time (using old “boring” tech, common sense workflow)
    </p>

    <p>- low learning curve</p>

    <p>
      - productive workflow (that's fun [/ not a drag] but also responsible)
    </p>

    <p>
      - application / structure that's easy to understand (and modify, maintain)
      (simple structure, focused on business logic)
    </p>

    <p>
      - Encouraging expedient technical decisions - focused on making shit
      happen [providing business value] fast, do what you need to do and don’t
      worry about, focus on solving a problem / meeting functional requirement
      (business logic) in the fastest and easiest way Favor practicality over
      perceived correctness
    </p>

    <h2>??</h2>

    <p>
      <b>the un-framework</b> &mdash; it has the opinions of a framework, but it's
      not actually a framework
    </p>

    <p><b>all this complexity</b> &mdash; is it really necessary?</p>
    <img
      class="w-100"
      src="/images/analogy-complexity.jpg"
      alt="all this complexity ... is it really necessary?"
    />
  </article>
</Layout>
